08/06/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Chief Prosecutor Boris Velchev said on Wednesday (7 June) that he came away with very bad impressions from the inspection he ordered at the supreme prosecutor's offices when he assumed his post in February. 
He threatened to dole out disciplinary action and promised similar inspections at regional prosecutor's offices.
In other news, Bulgarian, German and Austrian anti-crime agencies smashed an international cigarette smuggling network in a joint operation Wednesday, following a three-year investigation. 
Some 93 people, including 16 Bulgarians, were reportedly involved in the ring. 
(Mediapool, bTV - 07/06/06)
